data.title: Wedding of Archduchess Marie Christine of Austria, 2008

data.text:
Embed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty ImagesEmbed from Getty Images

Happy 10th Anniversary to Archduchess Marie-Christine of Austria (wearing a Yves Dooms with the antique Habsburg Veil and the Luxembourg Small Floral Tiara), daughter of Archduke Carl-Christian of Austria and Princess Marie-Astrid of Luxembourg, and Count Rodolphe of Limburg-Stirum, who got married on this day in 2008, at the ‘Sint-Romboutskathedraal’ (St. Rumbolds Cathedral) in Mechelen, Belgium, followed by a Reception at the Mechelen City Hall. The couple now have three sons.

Embed from Getty Images

Royal Guests and Relatives included Grand Duke Henri and Grand Duchess Maria Theresa of Luxembourg (aunt and uncle of the bride), Queen Fabiola (great-aunt) and Crown Prince Philippe of Belgium (cousin), Archduke Lorenz of Austria-Este and Princess Astrid of Belgium (both cousins of the bride), among members of the Habsburg and Grand Ducal Family and the European Nobility.
